      "writtenOn": "2020-08-25T02:06:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This file is a bit long. Let\u0027s try to make them compact.\n\nFor example, we can consolidate unit tests using only a single config file into one unit test case with subtests.\n\n func TestResolveHostFromFilesSingleConfig(t *testing.T) {\n   for _, tc :\u003d range []struct {\n     name   string // test case name\n     config string // config file content\n     host   string // input host name\n     want   string // expected resolved host name\n   }{\n     {\n       name:   \"first match wins\",\n       config: \"Host hana\\nHostname a\\nPort 1\\nHost hana\\nHostname b\\nPort 2\\n\",\n       host:   \"hana\",\n       want:   \"a:1\",\n     },\n     ...\n   } {\n     t.Run(tc.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n       ...\n     })\n   }\n }\n\nWe may still need to write separate unit tests for those using multiple config files. For those cases, we may still be able to make them shorter by introducing more utility functions.",
      "revId": "63725d75145496d2cb78708d1583516510893874",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
