      "lineNbr": 892,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-25T02:06:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In usual Go calling conventions, for a function that returns (T, error), T value should not be read if non-nil error is returned. There are a few exceptions to this rule (e.g. io.Reader.Read https://godoc.org/io#Reader), but in such cases it should be noted explicitly in comments.\n\nSo in this case I do recommend calling t.Fatalf instead to abort test execution without inspecting resolvedHost, or calling \"return\" immediately after t.Errorf (if we want to continue).",
